        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Integrating text-to-speech (TTS) into production systems often requires balancing voice customization, latency, and scalability. Off-the-shelf TTS services may not support brand-specific voices, while building custom models from scratch involves prohibitive costs and complexity. The Qwen3 TTS CustomVoice Multi-Model API solves this by providing a multi-model architecture that enables voice cloning with minimal latency, built on the Qwen3 TTS 12Hz 1.7B model for high-quality 12 kHz synthesis."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This API is designed for teams that need to deploy custom voices at scale, such as in interactive voice response (IVR) systems, audiobook generation, or real-time gaming. In this post, we'll cover the API's core capabilities, walk through integration with runnable code, analyze performance metrics, and break down costs. You'll gain actionable insights to implement and optimize the Qwen3 TTS CustomVoice Multi-Model API in your stack."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Capabilities of Qwen3 TTS CustomVoice Multi-Model API"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Qwen3 TTS CustomVoice Multi-Model API supports multi-model inference, allowing you to switch between different voice profiles or languages within a single API endpoint. It leverages the Qwen3 TTS 12Hz 1.7B model, which is optimized for real-time applications with a sample rate of 12 kHz and a model size of 1.7 billion parameters. Key features include custom voice cloning from audio samples, support for multiple languages (e.g., English, Mandarin), and adjustable speech parameters like speed and pitch."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For production use, the API offers low-latency synthesis, typically under 200 ms for short phrases, and high throughput for batch processing. It also provides SSML (Speech Synthesis Markup Language) support for fine-grained control over pronunciation and emphasis. This makes it suitable for applications where voice consistency and quality are critical, such as customer service bots or media production."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h3",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Voice Customization Options"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Custom voice cloning is achieved by uploading reference audio clips and specifying parameters in the API request. You can control aspects like voice timbre, emotional tone, and speaking rate. The API returns synthesized audio in WAV or MP3 format, with configurable bitrates. For example, to clone a voice, you need at least 10 seconds of clean audio per speaker, and the model handles background noise reduction automatically."
          }
        ]
      },
